	<str name="Title">
		Process and device for treating sludge
	</str>
	<str name="Abstract">
		In a process and a device for the separation and removal especially of lacquer sludge from a lacquer-sludge/water mixture, the lacquer-sludge/water mixture or the like is exposed to a directed horizontal flow in a vessel in the region of the water surface. At the same time, in a preferably front horizontal-flow portion, an essentially upwardly directed air-bubble flow consisting of very fine air bubbles is generated in the water, so that the suspended lacquer particles on the one hand float to the water surface and on the other hand are fed by means of the directed horizontal flow to a sludge discharge device.
	</str>
